FBIS3-18295 "drweu040_q_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-040 Document Type:Daily Report 1 Mar 1994 TURKEY Erbakan Criticizes Ciller for Holding Rally TA2802201594 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1800 GMT 28 Feb 94 TA2802201594 Ankara TRT Television Network Language: Turkish Article Type:BFN [Announcer-read report over video] [Excerpt] Prosperity Party leader Necmettin Erbakan has said that the respect for Ataturk rally held in Istanbul today violates the election bans. At a news conference in Ankara, Erbakan said that permission was not requested for the rally 72 hours earlier, as required by the law, and therefore sufficient time was not given to the security forces to take the necessary measures. Erbakan charged that the prime minister organized this rally for political aims. He added: [Begin Erbakan recording] In order to gather a crowd, she invited all our students, all our workers, even all our prosecutors to attend the rally even though it was a working day. This is a violation of the law, it is a crime. On the other hand, the election period is on. [end recording] [passage omitted]
